<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" data-rte-preserve-empty="true" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"></p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://open.spotify.com/artist/6SrZNK0y69ecgDHshinRJ9?si=1PWF3IYES9qIlN-Pz_1hOw" target="_blank"><strong>Cheap Bleach</strong></a> followed with a heavier and moodier tone. Drawing on post-hardcore and emo influences, their set leaned into fuzzed-out guitars and pounding drums, with tracks like <em>“Swear”</em> and <em>“Tusks”</em> showing off a darker, introspective edge. They were slightly more reserved onstage but made an effort to introduce the rest of the lineup — a nice touch. With a new album expected soon, this set felt like a preview of something with a lot of potential.<br><br></p></div>

