</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://open.spotify.com/artist/3u3ahaV33JSAvIjMoFxS4n?si=47jWYoHaR0KmHYsdMqzScw" target="_blank"><strong>Mountain Peaks</strong></a> brought noise, atmosphere, and intensity in equal measure. The Norwich trio opened with screaming vocals over a backing track and didn’t let up for the next half hour. Their sound — a mix of screamo, emo, and shoegaze — hit hardest on songs like <em>“Stargazers”</em>, which featured a standout drum intro, and <em>“I’m Not Happy”</em>, which they dedicated to rock bands everywhere. The set was heavy but not without charm — there was dry humour between members, and the Furby moment at the end somehow made sense in context.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></p></div>

