   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1747465236987-NZ1BJLT0G82K88QO4MQX/%40snaptastic__+-+Elvana+-+O2+Brixton+-+09-05-2025+%2855%29.JPG?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1747465237929-MICD6HNDNRSDTHK8KDID/%40snaptastic__+-+Elvana+-+O2+Brixton+-+09-05-2025+%2856%29.JPG?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">When the final notes rang out, the floor was still bouncing and the energy in the room hung in the air like static. From the front barrier to the back of the balcony, the crowd had been on their feet all night, singing, dancing, and throwing themselves into every moment. As fans slowly filtered out into the Brixton night, confetti stuck to their shoes and wide smiles on their faces, the unmistakable sound of Elvis-meets-Nirvana mashups was still ringing in everyone’s ears—marking the end of a night that won’t be forgotten any time soon.</p></div><iframe width="200" height="113" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yMVRbKHR4Q8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen title="Elvana Live @ O2 Brixton 10.05.2025"></iframe>',
  'Elvana is a uk based Elvis fronted nirvana tribute band from Newcastle -upon- Tyne. Having already rocked multiple festivals including download and Glastonbury&nbsp; they returned to London to take on the mighty O2 Academy Brixton.',
  'Feats.',
  '2025-05-19 10:00:00',
  'Live Music, Gig Review, Artist Showcase, concert',
  '/images/articles/%40snaptastic__+-+Elvana+-+O2+Brixton+-+09-05-2025+%282%29.JPEG',
  'publish'
);
INSERT INTO articles (title, url_id, body, excerpt, author, publish_date, categories, cover_url, status) VALUES (
  'Eurovision Winners Maneskin Release Their New Album “Rush!” and Prove To The World That They’re Here To Stay!',
  'eurovision-winners-maneskin-release-their-new-album-rush-and-prove-to-the-world-that-theyre-here-to-stay',
  '[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="2500"]<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/d8c2d61c-05a2-490c-83b2-8c4de4de7bbb/39.jpg?format=original" alt=" Fabio Germinario (fabiogerminario) "/>  Fabio Germinario (fabiogerminario) [/caption] 
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Italian rock band Maneskin are bursting into the music scene out of nowhere after winning Eurovision for Italy in 2021 with over a 25 point lead. Their unique style, to the rest of the competition, forced them into the spotlight and got the world thinking, “Who are these guys? Why can''t we get enough of them?”. They continued to follow up, earning two top ten positions in the official charts in 2021, winning MTV’s best rock song for their “The four seasons” cover of Beggin’ as well as being nominated for “Best New Band” at the Grammys, where they will battle for the award later this year. After selling out shows across the world, including London''s Legendary o2 Arena to recently Collaborating with Rage Against The Machines legendary Tom Morello on their single “Gossip!”, It goes to show that these Glam Rock superstars are here to stay and that they’ve cemented their place in the modern rock world.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Their New 17 Track Album “Rush!”, released on the 20/01, sees the band exploring their sound with world renowned LA based producer Max Martin, Famous for his extensive career in the music industry working with acts from Ariana Grande and Taylor Swift to Usher and The Backstreet Boys. The band''s songwriting goes hand in hand with Martin''s tight production to create an album full of undeniably catchy hooks that will be sure to be stuck in your head whilst you go about your day.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">The track list also sees the band experimenting with guitar pedals and various production effects, taking the band to the unfamiliar practices of previous records. They Utilised this in order to create a unique atmosphere with each track. This follows their recent listening to Radiohead during the writing process. Frontman Damiano said to NME “I think that the inspiration we got from Radiohead was to be very focused on creating a very specific world for each song. It''s something they do very, very well so we tried to create these amazing atmospheres”&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">This is especially apparent in tracks like “The Loneliest”, a Heartbreaking ballad that Beautifully explores death and loss with a soundscape incredibly reminiscent of their influence.&nbsp;</p></div>


  
      <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/4c15a4be-4411-42d4-b20f-96e473db5043/80.jpg?format=original" alt=""/>
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">They were also sure to mix in some of their biggest hits. “ZITTE E BUONI”, the Italian rock song that had catapulted the band into their success at Eurovision. The performance had everybody in the room moving so much, the ground shook below your feet. The crowd shouted every lyric word for word creating a raw live atmosphere that transcended language barriers. This was then followed by the cult favorite cover of “BEGGIN’”.</p></div>


  
      <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/def276e1-2609-436f-82de-531b98298380/67.jpg?format=original" alt=""/>
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Whether you love them or hate them it''s clear to see that Maneskin are here and they are here to stay.</p></div>


  
       [caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1867"]<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/e0382317-f995-4a5e-98ae-dec10f99f2f6/Copia+di+12.jpg?format=original" alt=" All Photos by Fabio Germinario (fabiogerminario)  "/>  All Photos by Fabio Germinario (fabiogerminario)  [/caption] 
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Tickets for their European Tour are available below:</p></div>



<!-- The Tour Dates Block is rendered by Handlebars. -->',
  'Italian Glam Rock band Maneskin cement their place in the music industry and prove their longevity beyond their Eurovision Win',
  'Feats.',
  '2023-01-31 12:02:00',
  'Album Release, Live Music, Review',
  '/images/articles/39.jpg',
  'publish'
);
INSERT INTO articles (title, url_id, body, excerpt, author, publish_date, categories, cover_url, status) VALUES (
  'Faetooth Live @ Norwich Arts Centre 19.06.2025',
  'faetooth-live-norwich-arts-centre-19-06-2025',
  '<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/310d2475-dc84-4f24-8082-d59b052bfcc6/%40shardsoflight_+-+Faetooth+-+Norwich+Arts+Centre+-+19.06.2025+-+005.jpg?format=original" alt=""/>
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Faetooth gathered probably the most packed crowd I’ve ever seen in the Arts Centre before, with their support acts ‘Kulk’ and ‘Cwfen’ doing more than just filling time - they were getting the crowd going, ready, and warming everyone up for a brilliant evening (or cooling seeing as there was many fans placed around the venue to keep the temperatures down!).&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">When Faetooth arrived on stage at 21:45 the crowd was ready to go, with the bands engaging and self proclaimed genre of ‘Fairy-doom’ drifting throughout the historic church venue, it truly felt like the most perfect setting for this genre, the sultry tones matching the warm temperature and deep purple lighting, combining with the venue to truly create a magical moment in time.</p></div>

<div class="image-gallery-wrapper">

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1750880331975-UPBCMEX9QFADZVF61U9Z/%40shardsoflight_+-+Faetooth+-+Norwich+Arts+Centre+-+19.06.2025+-+004.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
