   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1758299952329-KWHIOD45FSTWAO3926UL/%40jeffvad3r42+-+High+Regard+-+Camden+Underworld+-+11-09-2025+-+001.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1758299952465-PNVUM5POAR7PBNJGQ93J/%40jeffvad3r42+-+High+Regard+-+Camden+Underworld+-+11-09-2025+-+002.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1758299953785-VOPPTJNZVL480KV07TGR/%40jeffvad3r42+-+High+Regard+-+Camden+Underworld+-+11-09-2025+-+003.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Formed in Spokane, High Regard have carved out their own space in the scene with music that channels both aggression and honesty. Alongside McLean, guitarist Ryan Hare, bassist Gene Cavender and drummer Dan Knott deliver a sound that is uncompromising but full of conviction. Their Camden stop reinforced why they’re a band on the rise, and with more UK dates ahead — including shows in Leeds, Birmingham, and Cardiff — fans have plenty of chances to catch them bringing the same fire to stages across the country.</p></div><script charset="utf-8" src="https://widget.bandsintown.com/main.min.js"></script><a class="bit-widget-initializer" data-artist-name="High Regard" data-display-local-dates="false" data-display-past-dates="false" data-auto-style="false" data-text-color="#000000" data-link-color="#00b4b3" data-background-color="rgba(0,0,0,0)" data-display-limit="15" data-display-start-time="true" data-link-text-color="#FFFFFF" data-display-lineup="false" data-display-play-my-city="true" data-separator-color="rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5)"></a>',
  'High Regard brought their unrelenting hardcore energy to The Underworld in Camden as part of their latest run of shows. The night captured exactly what the band have become known for: raw intensity, a crowd that was fully involved from the first note, and a set that never once took its foot off the ',
  'Feats.',
