   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1746556371925-TAYICH40OLJWSG62GVQK/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Hilang+Child-+MothClub+-+02-05-2025-4++%285%29.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1746556371968-INHRIWWIRJE7SUG8O347/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Hilang+Child-+MothClub+-+02-05-2025-4++%286%29.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">It''s the penultimate night of Orchards UK tour, celebrating the release of their recent album Bicker which has taken them up and down the UK. Tonights show being at The Moth Club in Hackney</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Opening up the night is Hilang Child, recently joining Orchards as their new drummer tonights show gives him a chance to showcase his own music to the crowd. With the room starting to fill up it gave a more mellow calmer start to the night. With an accompanying track, he showed off both his drumming and vocal abilities to the crowd who started to make their way towards the stage. Playing a few unreleased tracks it was a solid start to the night.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Up next Congratulations, with more of a lively and upbeat sound. With a lot of energy from the band on stage it wasn’t too hard for them to get the crowd engaged and moving as well. With a ton of personality radiating from the band and a mix of bouncy songs it had spirits and energy high.</p></div>

