INSERT INTO articles (title, url_id, body, excerpt, author, publish_date, categories, cover_url, status) VALUES (
  'We caught up with Star Print Clad before their headline set at Green Door Store - here’s what they had to say',
  'star-print-clad-greendoor-interview-14-07-2025',
  '<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Fresh off their headline gig at <strong>Green Door Store</strong>, Brighton five-piece <strong>Star Print Clad</strong> are proving themselves as one of the city’s most exciting new live acts. Before they took to the stage, we caught up with the band to talk influences, favourite tracks, and what comes next.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><a href="https://open.spotify.com/artist/6fWft7li84u7nfLQII3oOY?si=AfhZOctiR4yY6Ygzzo7SeA"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><strong>Star Print Clad</strong></span></a><strong>; </strong>made up of <strong>Joseph (guitar &amp; vocals), Anthony (bass), Otto (drums), Tom (keys), and Jared (guitar)</strong>-describe themselves as an indie rock’n’roll band with their roots firmly planted in the sounds of the seventies.</p></div>


  
       [caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1280"]<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/97aeb0bc-dfb6-4dc5-be82-a15f6614f612/WhatsApp+Image+2025-07-14+at+10.25.38_e91b4db8.jpg?format=original" alt=" Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals "/>  Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals [/caption] 
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>“We’re a five-piece based in Brighton, taking a lot of influences from the seventies,” they told us. “We’re really into the whole harmony work and jagged sound the instruments held around then.”</em></p></div><hr /><div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">With their Green Door show looming, we asked which tracks they were most excited to bring to the stage.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>“I’m looking forward to </em><strong><em>Actor</em></strong><em>,”</em> said Joseph, further adding;<em> “We came out of the studios tracking it recently and I think it carries the soul of the band in a nutshell. You can really throw the song about live.”<br></em>Jared added, <em>“I’d say </em><a href="https://open.spotify.com/track/4nydO9fXwbeAnjKoNKCDIJ?si=cb93acc0600241f1"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><strong><em>Angel in Evergreen</em></strong></span></a><strong><em>.</em></strong><em> It really drives the energy up in the set, and writing the part with Tom was a great creative moment. It gives a Kings of Leon vibe.”</em></p></div><hr />


  
       [caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1280"]<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/ce8a16b6-02d9-4368-92f3-d7a87f0c546c/WhatsApp+Image+2025-07-14+at+10.25.38_4ef9c26c.jpg?format=original" alt=" Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals "/>  Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals [/caption] 
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">The band had just released their latest single, <em>Serene</em>, and we couldn’t help but ask what might be next-an album? A tour?</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>“As much as we’d love a full tour-and hey, if anyone’s planning one, you can contact our management-we’re cutting our teeth and plotting at the minute. We’re trying to screw our heads into a consistent release schedule for singles and ramp up our live shows to tackle as many as possible September onwards.”</em></p></div><hr /><div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">As always at Feats., we finished on a dream feature question-if they could collaborate with <em>anyone</em>, dead or alive, who would it be?</p></div>


  
       [caption id="" align="alignnone" width="719"]<img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/f65f0181-d2e1-4f05-82b2-b21086034259/WhatsApp+Image+2025-07-14+at+10.25.39_9d9a2c57.jpg?format=original" alt=" Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals "/>  Photo Credit: Paddy Collier / @pjc.visuals [/caption] 
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>“George Harrison,” they all agreed. “We think he had a beautiful melodic mind. Honest songs, great character, greater clothes. It’d be an incredibly insightful session. Might finally learn how to play slide guitar.”</em></p></div><hr /><div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">And finally, where can we catch you next?</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"><em>“Next show, Good Vibrations Festival-that’ll be a good one. All of our socials are </em><a href="https://www.instagram.com/starprintclad"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><strong><em>@starprintclad</em></strong></span></a><em>. Cheers Feats, hope to catch you soon x.”</em></p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Keep your eyes on <strong>Star Print Clad</strong>-if their set at Green Door Store is anything to go by, this is just the beginning.</p></div><iframe style="border-radius:12px" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/artist/6fWft7li84u7nfLQII3oOY?utm_source=generator" width="100%" height="352" frameBorder="0" allowfullscreen="" allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy"></iframe>',
  'Fresh off their headline gig at Green Door Store, Brighton five-piece Star Print Clad are proving themselves as one of the city’s most exciting new live acts. Before they took to the stage, we caught up with the band to talk influences, favourite tracks, and what comes next.',
  'Feats.',
  '2025-07-18 10:00:00',
  'Interview, Live Music, ONES TO WATCH, Artist Showcase',
  '/images/articles/WhatsApp+Image+2025-07-14+at+10.25.38_e91b4db8.jpg',
  'publish'
);
INSERT INTO articles (title, url_id, body, excerpt, author, publish_date, categories, cover_url, status) VALUES (
  'Stratford Rise at the Windmill 31.07.2025',
  'stratford-rise-at-the-windmill-31-07-2025',
  '<div class="image-gallery-wrapper">

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507084021-V30WCPEPL810SPU4LVC0/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+005.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507084145-JW29T0LOEHPR7GVWMR50/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+006.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507085213-4RJHZU1C2QXCETOTTYP9/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+007.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507085338-EDETZ6Q7SK0JMLMI03XG/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+008.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507086741-NF2WN0H7XP8AAIXCV2LE/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+009.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507087097-10QWP2F0MQIVNMR7U5E7/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+010.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507087822-4A8I1PYHMJ4VILL8DLZU/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+001.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507088366-X0UX715WBAMESPW7FCQ9/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+002.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507089067-6D00897RX6YYGOWR4M1D/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+003.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507089452-NE1HY08YV32570PH2I0I/%40fox_trotter42+-+Thorby+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+004.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">On the final day of July, Stratford Rise took to the Windmill for their first ever London show in support of their debut EP. Playing with them was Thorby and Slowhandclap, the latter also playing their first London show.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Thorby opened up the night slowly and calmly, with a short electronic set to ease everybody in. Hands constantly shifting dials and pressing buttons to create a set of beats, constantly changing and evolving, with the audience visibly nodding along as the set passes swiftly by.</p></div><hr />

<div class="image-gallery-wrapper">

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507108255-XFY1SDEE85I1E9L3Y5TB/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+004.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507108482-MR31TYYRNII1STSNA0UJ/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+005.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507109679-26M5EGMZ64CS2TSXMJZX/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+006.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507110335-8LE6TXS3JE6UXEU2J50P/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+007.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507111077-JVQX8XOO6PSIY08SPYU9/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+008.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507111700-WY1OKD27CGY3WFEHMNXU/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+009.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507113034-I6FJV53CCUQMVTNXK6AI/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+010.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507113165-UPKWR36HKGJAO7HO54EA/%40fox_trotter42+-+Slowhandclap+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+001.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">With a shift in genres, Slowhandclap followed Thorby with a take on noise rock that leans a lot more into the noise part than the rock. Distorted layers of bass and guitar, interspersed with slabs of industrial abrasivity, fill up the room as a few members of the crowd start jumping about. While they were only the openers, Slowhandclap is an essential find for anybody who likes anything as gritty as it is intense.</p></div><hr />


  
      <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/ae3c62a7-1cac-4d65-8a05-8d3574bbf8a1/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+004.jpg?format=original" alt=""/>
  

<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Half an hour later, Stratford Rise took to the stage and 30 seconds after created a wall of noise unmistakeable as the intro to ‘Gunshow’, the first song of their eponymous debut EP. The crowd, chanting along to the first few riffs, started a powerful pit absorbing all of the floor space of the Windmill as chaos ensued. Both the band and the crowd continued to indulge in madness as the next song on the EP, ‘Prone’, only increased the energy with even more dissonance, more frenetic riffs and grooves, and more lines sung by the crowd. It now reached a point where the singer had to warn the crowd to not get too close to the stage and to make sure the amps didn’t fall onto the dozens of pedals responsible for creating the myriad of tones produced by every instrument.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">The pauses to tune the instruments between every song gave a much needed respite to the crowd during the hour-long set and were always filled with jokes and banter between band and audience. A cover of the song ‘Detached’, by the classic New York based no wave band DNA, showcased their influences when creating experimental onslaughts of sound. A long line of thank yous led into their debut single ‘Running Water Through Faucet’, which breathed new energy into the now very sweaty and tired crowd, ending the performance. </p></div>

<div class="image-gallery-wrapper">

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507159046-WWKJK9ZUO9VNANB9JF9R/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+014.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507159353-X253K8H708IUKV4JH0PZ/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+015.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507160335-9S13VGUIHWR4GCDZ5XXV/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+016.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507160488-V0V01MKWA1X74SO2EYBM/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+017.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507161667-WDY4WDF306EIA1OZPD9M/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+018.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507161985-HV3J6YYANVK63GLMN4CU/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+019.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507163111-KLIYVKP393V6F42ZUH7I/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+020.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507167181-UAABUSRVO1IJ6WR3M488/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+001.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507167751-N3EZC635KZQNIXIOPH8N/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+002.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507168548-FVZ92613UJ1L7AXATE27/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+003.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507169255-DWM7U4P2WDSPFOXHTF08/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+004.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507169920-EZV1UUN15LDCZVG08LRE/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+005.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507171032-YGCZHSMD6UH2TPU7G0BQ/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+006.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507171383-OTGOQTLI0PMLVW4C2UXJ/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+007.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507172548-8GVVJ4557EA70F7X1Q3C/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+008.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507173075-3205QJTK12GYTY31T6P1/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+009.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507174286-OD0Z1ZD1TRBK3BU8T3R7/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+010.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507174715-DXIFJQYI59ZL5FC21SR7/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+011.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507175645-01HE0KCMPEGWEKWZ7LO0/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+012.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1754507176281-NE9IJJ1NMYEBMQ1XAFMD/%40fox_trotter42+-+Stratford+Rise+-+The_Windmill+-+31-07-2025+-+013.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">It is now abundantly clear that Stratford Rise is a must listen for everyone who craves the Schlagenheim-era craziness of Black Midi, but taken to whole new heights. An unmissable live act.</p></div>',
  'On the final day of July, Stratford Rise took to the Windmill for their first ever London show in support of their debut EP. Playing with them was Thorby and Slowhandclap, the latter also playing their first London show.',
  'Feats.',
