   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953714823-IO61NW5HPEJJE0ST4A6O/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+010.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953716028-Y1CVXZCFZQJIOXAVL6E2/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+011.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953716044-TFA7H0FNKM9MAM2RHVD0/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+012.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953717326-ZTATF36DRM3IVOSCBZR6/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+013.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953717406-CZYJ3FKKNY2X2RVFT48P/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+014.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953718601-BRLHI0UXCCAM3Z9SFVR3/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+015.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953718844-H72VRX6UV9JBOA8CWHEU/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Pollyanna+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+016.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Opening the night was ''Pollyanna''. Giving a more calmer and chill start to the evening. Opening with track The Chase her music was very acoustically driven while also being supported by her band. The set was filled with personality, from making effort to engage with the crowd, with some songs being heavily influenced by film and TV which has the audience play a game of guessing the influence of track ''The Beach''&nbsp; </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">A bit of a contrast to Pollyanna, Love Rarely brought a more heavier and aggressive sound to the night. With a lot of people already familiar with them, they were able to command the stage with a strong presence and a ton of energy. Making sure they finished the night gaining some more fans.</p></div>

