   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953747532-HE52WPEH67JJ4BT61XY4/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Love+Rarely+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+008.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953749016-75Q0O3L5KOAKQFH8EDIN/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Love+Rarely+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+009.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953748946-J3W4QERR1L3OMDZTGHCN/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Love+Rarely+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+010.jpg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953750552-ZSEGQBZL9E4QVJLK1CFR/image-asset.jpeg?format=original" />
  

  
   <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/627907a6b74722549de2ec0c/1748953750730-9N3TJW9LNINN5XIUI295/%40c.shoots.shows+-+Love+Rarely+-+Downstairs+At+The+Dome+-+28-05-2025+-+012.jpg?format=original" />
  

</div>
<div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">The room now full with fans Sweet Pill took to the stage. Keeping up the energy from earlier on in the night. The captivating set was full of fan favourite tracks but also a few unreleased songs thrown into the mix. While they may have been unfamiliar with the fans in the room, each one was received positively. In between songs the band took their chance to interact with the crowd, especially with some friendly banter about “British Traditions’ such as Greggs and Wetherspoons. Throughout the night you could see the connection between the band and the crowd, from people singing back lyrics and the crowd trying to keep up and match the energy on stage. It was only a year ago that Sweet Pill was opening this room, but they have more then proved why they are now headlining it themselves. With new music on the horizon and an already established base of core fans the future of Sweet Pill is looking bigger and brighter</p></div>

